s"},{"pid":"e176d6d7c107763f025ad5b12f12c7c2ae2bddaa","tid":2095154,"uid":154984,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"fec57997d98d1f4fa2549f2ddc762de154c4c645","tid":2095154,"uid":79563,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"85593052713e4cc9626641bacf4f54b2c36b9d49","tid":2095154,"uid":335434,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"2167b8b28a5e2d42064437a90c4a69b1a309a864","tid":2095154,"uid":79563,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-07-06T10:02:07.000Z","msg":"都唔係咁<br />\n<br />\n你做吓research先"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-07-06T10:07:16.000Z","msg":"即係你覺得香港堆ETO嘅駐海外公務員有diplomatic immunity??"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-07-06T10:12:10.000Z","msg":"各國自己有法案grant咗diplomatic immunity<br />\n<br />\n你自己去research啦, 叫你又唔撚去做, 問問問, 餵埋你好無?<br />\n<br />\n英國《香港經濟貿易文化辦事處法案1996》<br />\n<br />\n加拿大《香港經濟貿易文化辦事處特權及豁免權命令》<br />\n<br />\n澳州《香港經濟貿易文化辦事處(特權及豁免權)規例1996》<br />\n<br />\n美國 United States Senate, A Bill to Extend Certain Privileges, Exemptions and Immunities to Hong Kong Economic and Trade Offices"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-07-06T10:14:52.000Z","msg":"香港政府使唔使驅逐埋美國領事館出境<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"03a71aed3f8dfd22b80d3b870851e135f792c8c2","tid":2095154,"uid":79563,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-07-06T10:16:15.000Z","msg":"<strong><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\"><span style=\"color: red;\">Hong Kong Economic and Trade Office Privileges and Immunities Order<br />\nSOR/96-207</span></span></strong><br />\n<br />\nShort Title<br />\n1 This Order may be cited as the Hong Kong Economic and Trade Office Privileges and Immunities Order.<br />\n<br />\nPrivileges and Immunities<br />\n2 The privileges and immunities accorded to<strong><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\"><span style=\"color: red;\"> consular posts </span></span></strong>under <strong><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\"><span style=\"color: red;\">section 3 of the Foreign Missions and International Organizations Act</span></span></strong> are hereby granted to the Hong Kong Economic and Trade Office, and persons connected therewith, in Canada including members of their families forming part of their households in Canada, who are not nationals or permanent residents of Canada.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<strong><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\">Foreign Missions and International Organizations Act</span></strong><br />\n<br />\nForeign Diplomatic Missions and Consular Posts<br />\nMarginal note:Conventions on diplomatic relations and consular relations<br />\n<br />\n<strong><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\">3 (1)</span></strong> Articles 1, 22 to 24 and 27 to 40 of the Vienna Convention on Diplomatic Relations, and Articles 1, 5, 15, 17, 31 to 33, 35, 39 and 40, paragraphs 1 and 2 of Article 41, Articles 43 to 45 and 48 to 54, paragraphs 2 and 3 of Article 55, paragraph 2 of Article 57, paragraphs 1 to 3 of Article 58, Articles 59 to 62, 64, 66 and 67, paragraphs 1, 2 and 4 of Article 70 and Article 71 of the<strong><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\"><span style=\"color: red;\"> Vienna Convention</span></span></strong> on Consular Relations, have the force of law in Canada in respect of all foreign states, regardless of whether those states are parties to those Conventions."},{"pid":"4f70a3a678d75ec276919983bd13d6d22e4a533f","tid":2095154,"uid":79563,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"03a71aed3f8dfd22b80d3b870851e135f792c8c2","tid":2095154,"uid":79563,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-07-06T10:16:15.000Z","msg":"<strong><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\"><span style=\"color: red;\">Hong Kong Economic and Trade Office Privileges and Immunities Order<br />\nSOR/96-207</span></span></strong><br />\n<br />\nShort Title<br />\n1 This Order may be cited as the Hong Kong Economic and Trade Office Privileges and Immunities Order.<br />\n<br />\nPrivileges and Immunities<br />\n2 The privileges and immunities accorded to<strong><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\"><span style=\"color: red;\"> consular posts </span></span></strong>under <strong><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\"><span style=\"color: red;\">section 3 of the Foreign Missions and International Organizations Act</span></span></strong> are hereby granted to the Hong Kong Economic and Trade Office, and persons connected therewith, in Canada including members of their families forming part of their households in Canada, who are not nationals or permanent residents of Canada.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<strong><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\">Foreign Missions and International Organizations Act</span></strong><br />\n<br />\nForeign Diplomatic Missions and Consular Posts<br />\nMarginal note:Conventions on diplomatic relations and consular relations<br />\n<br />\n<strong><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\">3 (1)</span></strong> Articles 1, 22 to 24 and 27 to 40 of the Vienna Convention on Diplomatic Relations, and Articles 1, 5, 15, 17, 31 to 33, 35, 39 and 40, paragraphs 1 and 2 of Article 41, Articles 43 to 45 and 48 to 54, paragraphs 2 and 3 of Article 55, paragraph 2 of Article 57, paragraphs 1 to 3 of Article 58, Articles 59 to 62, 64, 66 and 67, paragraphs 1, 2 and 4 of Article 70 and Article 71 of the<strong><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\"><span style=\"color: red;\"> Vienna Convention</span></span></strong> on Consular Relations, have the force of law in Canada in respect of all foreign states, regardless of whether those states are parties to those Conventions."},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-07-06T10:17:21.000Z","msg":"冚家產, 比晒HINT叫你條仆街去RESEARCH<br />\n對手廢既？ 要餵既？<br />\n<br />\n食啦仆街<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://laws-lois.justice.gc.ca/eng/regulations/SOR-96-207/page-1.html#h-980433\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Flaws-lois.justice.gc.ca%2Feng%2Fregulations%2FSOR-96-207%2Fpage-1.html%23h-980433&d=yjoviXv3Qi